The eight edition of the annual Gtbank Masters Cup reaches final stage after eight schools took part in the semi final matches which were played on Monday at the Campus Mini Stadium, Lagos. Kings College secured their glory by earning a 4-0 amazing victory over Whitesands School at the competition. Despite the early Monday’s downpour, Kings College boys didn’t look to take their opponent easy as they thrashed Whitesand boys 4 goals to null to book a final match against Anwar Ul Islam Model College, Agege which outshined CMS Grammer School in an amazing 1-0 win, after penalty was awarded to both teams. For the females match, Leadforte College took down Ansar-UD-Deen Girls High School, Itire in a 2-1 to book a final place with Queens College who defeated Atlantic Hall Epe with a walkover. Ansar ud deen Girls were sharper after the break which led to their one goal but Leadforte College got down smartly earning a victory lead. Gtbank, as usual, reiterated the need to give sports especially football the best support they can stating that this will tackle indiscipline and reduce social vices amongst the youths in the society. This includes promoting the development of sports, as the bank retains their sponsorship of the football programme. 